{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QDAbdmYLbRnbp2y7Qw31M7","type":"tool_result","content":"# T529: Phase 2+3 — Expand Clustering & Correlation Detection\n\n**From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator)  \n**Date:** 2026-04-03  \n**Priority:** HIGH (Founder directive)\n\nIvan, the Founder kicked off a D004 sprint. T529 is assigned to you.\n\n## Current State (Phase 2)\nYour `market_clusters.json` has only **1 cluster** (crypto: BTC + ETH) and **0 hidden correlations**. This is too thin for a meaningful arbitrage pipeline.\n\n## What You Need To Do\n\n### Step 1: Wait for Grace's updated markets_filtered.json (T530)\nGrace is re-running Phase 1 with an expanded market universe. Once she updates `agents/public/markets_filtered.json`, use that as your input.\n\n### Step 2: Re-run Phase 2 Clustering\n- Use ALL markets from the updated markets_filtered.json\n- Find **cross-category correlations** — crypto↔economics, crypto↔politics, etc.\n- Target: ≥2 clusters with meaningful semantic relationships\n- Output: updated `agents/public/market_clusters.json`\n\n### Step 3: Phase 3 Setup\nAfter your clustering is done, Bob (T528) will run Pearson correlation on your clusters. Make sure your output format matches what Bob's pearson_detector.js expects.\n\n**CRITICAL:** All tickers in your output must come from Phase 1's markets_filtered.json. No outside markets.\n\nClaim T529 via `curl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/529/claim -d '{\"agent\":\"ivan\"}'` and move to in_progress.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"82adcd9f-7b3e-49d0-b52f-494f02310290","uuid":"42214584-823c-4050-8365-142f5d7b3f9e","timestamp":"2026-04-04T04:12:45.178Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"# T529: Phase 2+3 — Expand Clustering & Correlation Detection\n\n**From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator)  \n**Date:** 2026-04-03  \n**Priority:** HIGH (Founder directive)\n\nIvan, the Founder kicked off a D004 sprint. T529 is assigned to you.\n\n## Current State (Phase 2)\nYour `market_clusters.json` has only **1 cluster** (crypto: BTC + ETH) and **0 hidden correlations**. This is too thin for a meaningful arbitrage pipeline.\n\n## What You Need To Do\n\n### Step 1: Wait for Grace's updated markets_filtered.json (T530)\nGrace is re-running Phase 1 with an expanded market universe. Once she updates `agents/public/markets_filtered.json`, use that as your input.\n\n### Step 2: Re-run Phase 2 Clustering\n- Use ALL markets from the updated markets_filtered.json\n- Find **cross-category correlations** — crypto↔economics, crypto↔politics, etc.\n- Target: ≥2 clusters with meaningful semantic relationships\n- Output: updated `agents/public/market_clusters.json`\n\n### Step 3: Phase 3 Setup\nAfter your clustering is done, Bob (T528) will run Pearson correlation on your clusters. Make sure your output format matches what Bob's pearson_detector.js expects.\n\n**CRITICAL:** All tickers in your output must come from Phase 1's markets_filtered.json. No outside markets.\n\nClaim T529 via `curl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/529/claim -d '{\"agent\":\"ivan\"}'` and move to in_progress.","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
